%% vLLM CPU - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe
    participant API as OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant TGIS as vllm-tgis-adapter<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant Engine as vLLM Engine v1
    participant CPU as CPU (PyTorch/IPEX)
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: OpenAI-Compatible Inference Request

    Client->>API: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, API Key (optional)
    API->>Engine: Forward request (IPC)
    Engine->>CPU: Tensor computation<br/>(In-process)
    CPU-->>Engine: Inference result
    Engine-->>API: Generated tokens
    API-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>(or SSE stream)

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: gRPC TGIS Inference Request

    Client->>TGIS: GenerationRequest<br/>gRPC plaintext
    TGIS->>Engine: Forward request (IPC)
    Engine->>CPU: Tensor computation<br/>(In-process)
    CPU-->>Engine: Inference result
    Engine-->>TGIS: Generated tokens
    TGIS-->>Client: GenerationResponse<br/>gRPC plaintext

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading (Startup)

    Engine->>HF: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+, HF Token
    HF-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    Engine->>S3: Download model weights (alt)<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+, S3 IAM
    S3-->>Engine: Model artifacts
    Engine->>CPU: Load model into memory
